{"word":"G2508 - καθαίρω - kathaírō - kath-ah'-ee-ro - Purge","slug":"G2508","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">καθαίρω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>kathaírō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kath-ah'-ee-ro"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Purge"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"- Original: <b><el>καθαίρω</el></b> <p />- Transliteration: <b>Kathairo</b> <p />- Phonetic: <b>kath-ah'-ee-ro</b> <p class=\"def\">- Definition: </p> <p class='li260'><b>1.</b> to cleanse, of filth impurity, etc </p> <p class='li520'><b>a.</b> to prune trees and vines from useless shoots </p> <p class='li520'><b>b.</b> metaph. from guilt, to expiate </p> <p class=\"origin\"/>- Origin: from <a href=\"#/G2513\">G2513</a> <p />- TDNT entry: 09:53,4 <p />- Part(s) of speech: Verb <p />- Strong's: From <a href=\"#/G2513\">G2513</a>; to <i>cleanse</i> that is (specifically) to <i>prune</i>; figuratively to <b><i>expiate</i></b>: - purge. "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1571\">G1571</a>, <a href=\"#/G167\">G167</a>, <a href=\"#/G168\">G168</a>, <a href=\"#/G169\">G169</a>, <a href=\"#/G2511\">G2511</a>, <a href=\"#/G2512\">G2512</a>, <a href=\"#/G2513\">G2513</a>, <a href=\"#/G2514\">G2514</a>, <a href=\"#/G4027\">G4027</a>"}]}